column12: Enough horseplay!
We lost a good deal of time with that.
...Yeah.
If this room truly contains the power to control all magic,
I can use it to cure my eyes.
If we could heal both Emil and Kainé at once, it would be quite an achievement. Two birds with one, er...stone...as they say.
Wow, Weiss. I didn't think you cared.
Perhaps this tome is getting a bit sappy in his old age!
It should be right around here somewhere...
Sheathe your weapon! A physical blow would doubtless harm the boy!
We must use magic to defeat this beast!
Emil! We're coming for you!
Come back to us!
No! Don't! Don't look at me!
Emil, what's wrong?
Stay back!
Hurry! There's still time to save him!
I know there is!
What anger this creature must have! How did it even survive these past five years!?
I'm not going to let this happen again. It dies today!
My sword feels...lighter!
It's not the blade, but the skill of the user!<LF>Strike it down!
The path above the entrance to the shopping district should take me to the boat landing.
The Junk Heap... Perhaps we should speak to the brothers.
They might know something about this.
It's a shame about the older lad. He was but a child.
Sounds like he went into a dangerous area for the sake of the business.
The elder brother postponed his joy for the sake of his sibling.<LF>...Do you think he was ever truly happy?
Just making his little brother happy would have been enough.<LF>That's what being an older brother is like.
I've never heard of a Shade living with a machine. What's that about?
Don't know, don't care. All that matters is that we kill them both.
Looks like we found 'em.
Good lord, it's enormous!
Intruder detected. Scanning... Scanning... Exterminating.
Do it, Beepy! Beat 'em good!
Look at the Shade!
That thing is commanding the robot somehow!
Aim for the legs! Knock it down!
Take out the Shade!
Exterminating...ing...ing...ing...ing...
Beepy, wait! That's enough!
You're gonna be destroyed if you keep fighting!
Must...defend... My...mission...
No! I can't live without you!
I don't wanna be alone again!
No, dammit! That's a Shade... It's a Shade!
Kah hah hah hah hah! Kill him! KILL HIM! Feel the hate inside you!
This thing can transform!?
Beepy! What are you doing?
Escape, escape, escape, escape...
Go...see the world-ld-ld-ld.
Wait! No! You can stop now! You've done enough!
Must protect... Must fight...
Stop! Beepy's my best friend in the whole world! Stop hurting him!
Error-r-r-r-r-r...
You took everything from me! You killed my brother... You killed my mother! If it weren't for you they'd still be ALIVE!
This is all too easy!
You're telling me.
Turn back! Turn back!
What's with these guys?
Certainly not your garden-variety Shades.
Their bodies aren't fully functional.
Say, I've heard of this! A cursed area where incomplete Shades gather!
Kainé? Emil? Look, from now on, I'm going to sleep outside with you.
Why?
I can't accept that you aren't allowed in the village. It's stupid.
So you're staging a protest? Fun!
Don't waste your time.
But it just feels...wrong.
Well, that's really nice of you, but you still don't have to stay out here with us.
Emil...
You've got a super important mission! You can't sleep out in the rain—what if you catch a cold?
Besides, I like camping with Kainé! Sometimes we sit around the fire and tell stories, or roast—
Emil, that's enough! ...I got a fucking image to maintain.
We seem to be surrounded by a mob of helpless puppies.
Just kick 'em aside.
Damn you!
What's going on? There's dozens of them!
Stop, little ones! They're too strong for you!
These are creatures of the darkness!<LF>Lure them to the light!
Pathetic to the end, I see.
Aim for that statue! It's the leader!
I am not their leader! It is I who rely on them!
It is they who saved me!
Stop hurting my friends!
Bwah hah hah! Oh, you're funny! I'm gonna start cryin' here!
Bwah hah hah hah! This is one stubborn son of a bitch!
Dammit, dammit, dammit!
Hey there, Sunshine! You ain't feeling bad for this freak, are ya?
Ain't no turnin' back now!
Ya gotta lust for blood! Embrace the slaughter!
All we know is the thrill of battle! Ain't that right, Kainé?
Kainé!
Move... Move! Come on, you stupid arm, move!
We are incomplete. But our friends make us whole!
We are mocked, abused, and hated. But our friends keep us strong!
That is what keeps us going!
Do not stand in the way of our lives!
Those...are...my friends!
Come on, move! Move, move, move!
Hurry! Strike it down!
It's Kainé's Shade...
We've no other choice: We must strike it down!
Kainé! Come back!
Stop Kainé from acting!
It's do or die time!
Kaaah hah hah hah! I'll swallow you all!
Emil!
Kainé, please! Come back to us!
Aw, weddings are the best!
There's flowers everywhere, everyone's happy... It's just great!
I'm kinda jealous! Aren't you jealous, Kainé?
Meh.
Oh, come on!
That wolf is a Shade!
You razed our forests and poisoned our streams, and now you slaughter our young!
We will abide your existence no longer, mankind!
You will atone for your sins with blood!
(For the queen!)
The wolves appear to be targeting the king.
(Please be careful, my liege!)
(We must protect the king and his advisor!)
Such dogged, unwavering defiance!
Why do these beasts hold so much rage?
The smaller wolves are not infected with Shades. But as for the leader...
If even one Shade is here, then I have to kill all of 'em!
Above you! Stay on your guard!
He seeks the king of Facade!
The king is in danger!
I'll guard the king. That's what Fyra would want.
Indeed, you must worry about protecting more than yourself in this battle!
(Come, wolves! Taste the sting of our blades! I'll not leave a single one of you alive!)
We can never forgive you, humans!
There shall never be peace between us!
Never! Never! NEVER!
I cannot fathom that village setting up a mercantile.<LF>They must have truly opened their minds!
Yeah, I have my doubts.
First, we should ascertain where the letter came from.
Surely you're not planning to abandon those villagers?
They've been possessed somehow.
Keep your guard up! Others are surely lurking nearby.
You guys sure are taking your goddamn time.
A thousand apologies. We were distracted by the local welcoming party.
Want some help?
A carnival of murder? I love it! Kah hah hah hah hah!
Kainé, the villagers are possessed!
But not all of 'em! Some are still human, so be careful!
Dammit. It's a trap!
I figured as much!
Why have you done this!? We just wanted to live our lives in peace!
Stop it! Don't hurt my sister!
You monster! You possessed monster!
It is YOU who have lost your humanity! You are the true monsters!
What madness! These people are behaving as if we are the villains.
You are the cursed ones! You are the ones who should die!
Kainé!
Kainé!
Kill them! Kill them now!
No! You've gotta stop this!
We're trying to save you from the Shades!
Please, you have to stop!
Emil!
We need to get outta here! Kainé? Kainé, get up! Hurry!
Aw, the little vixen has finally run out of steam.
Is it my turn now? Are you suuure about that, Sunshine?
Grrrrrrrrraaaggggh!
Stop this at once!
Leave us in peace!
Hurry! The lad can't last long!
I know!
I'll try to pin it down!
Emil!
I can't do this anymore! Aaaaah!
Its weak point is located around the back!<LF>Try attacking it from above!
I marvel at how relatively simple a task this retrieval process proved to be.
It is almost as if someone deliberately set us on this path...
You're over-thinking again, Weiss.
But...
I don't care if it's a trap. Yonah's waiting for me, and I'm going.
...I see.
We should return to Popola and see if she has any final words for us.
Such an ominous sight. And yet I find it strangely nostalgic.
Yeah.
This is where Weiss and I first met—and first fought together.
Wow! This is where you used to live, Weiss!?
Well... Yes, I suppose. In a technical sense.
Pretty nice digs for a floating magazine.
At least it was free from annoying hussies like yourself!
Okay, hold on. Is it just me or are we looping around the same path over and over?
What do you mean?
Every beginning's an end, and every end's a beginning! Kya hah hah hah!
I think he means we're stuck.
There must be an escape route somewhere...
Well then! It seems the way is open.
Devola? What's happening!?
Sorry, but this fate was predetermined.
Still, we spoke to truth. We really wanted to avoid this if possible.
We were hoping to put it off for a hundred years or so. Until the next generation came along.
What are you talking about!?
Are they Shades?
I don't think so.
It's a lie! I don't believe it!
Kaaah hah hah hah! Kill 'em, you glorious bastards! Kill 'em all!
We never thought you'd grow to be this powerful.
This is madness! Why do you block our path?
You have no cause to speak so with us, Grimoire Weiss. You are a traitor!
Oh, shit on a shingle... They can use the Sealed Verses.
Of course we can! The power came from us in the first place!
You were simply loaned a small portion of it.
Grnnnhh...
Weiss! Are you all right?
Devola! Popola! Why are you guys doing this!?
Why are you siding with the Shades!?
They...c-copied...my powers...
Devola and Popola are fighting us...
Yes, they do seem to be putting us through a great deal of tuuur...<LF>Tuuub... Tr-tr-tuuurb...
You okay, Weiss?
How odd. For long years, my mind and tongue have been my greatest assets.
But now the latter seems to be faaa... Fa-fa-fa... Faaaiiil....
Weiss?
Do not look at me like that! I am Grimoire Weiss! I am perfectly fiiiiii... Fiiiiii...<LF>Fi-fi-fi-fi-fi-fiiiiiiiiiiii...
I think I hear a waltz.
Devola and Popola are fighting against us...
Yes, they do seem to be putting us through a great deal of tuuuur...<LF>Tuuubbb... Tr-tr-tuuurb...
You okay, Weiss?
How odd. For long years, my mind and tongue have been my greatest assets.
But now the latter seems to be faaa... Fa-fa-fa... Faaaiiil....
Weiss?
Do not look at me like that! I am Grimoire Weiss! I am perfectly fiiiii... Fiiiiiii...<LF>Fi-fi-fi-fi-fi-fiiiiiiiiiiiii...
It certainly is a grand affair!
Buncha dancin' bastards...
They're all Shades!
Defilers! None of you are human!
This is a holy sanctuary for humans! Leave at once, beasts!
I think we're locked in!
It's not like I was planning to leave.
Heh. Yeah, it's a bit late for that.
This sanctuary must remain under our protection.
It is our final bastion.
For the sake of those we love...
We will not allow it to be destroyed.
Dammit! They won't stop coming!
I'll open the next door! Cover me!
Oh, how I do love a good daaaaaa... Daaannn... Da-da-da-da—
Weiss!
...Mmm? Oh, right. Protect the hussy, yes? Good plan. Let's go.
Nooooo! Our treasures lie just beyond!
You can't enter! You mustn't!
Protect Kainé for us!
Stupid door... Come on. ...Oh, come on!
Kainé, hurry!
It's not open yet!?
Do I look like a goddamn locksmith to you!?
No! You idiot! What are you doing!?
Lock doesn't wanna open? Fine! I'll just break it down!
Stop, you impatient fool!
It certainly is a grand affair!
Buncha dancin' bastards...
They're all Shades!
Ah, a royal ball! How utterly d-diviii...dvvvvnnnn...
Waaaah!
Waaaaaah!
Are they...laughing?
These things are freaking me out!
Kainé! What's wrong!?
Stop! Please, stop!
They're just babies! They don't know any better!
Kainé! What's wrong!?
We waited for so long, and now we finally can recreate them...
We need to help Kainé!
Spare the lives of the children!
Please! I beg you!
There is no justice in the slaughter of innocents!
How many have you killed? How many? Your actions can never be forgiven!
We don't need forgiveness, asshole!
Kainé?
Wait a second. Waaaait a second! Your heart is...different.
It ain't hatred... And it ain't sadness... What's going on here, Sunshine?
How should I know!?
Kainé! Are you all right!?
I'm fine. Let's just kill some shit and move on, all right?
Iiinteresting. Oh, how very interesting!
Our attacks are not wor-or-or-orking.
I think we're in trouble.
This way! Move!
Up here!
Kaaah hah hah! Oh, you pissed her off now!
Maybe you shouldn't have killed her friends!
Look at her! So full of scorn and hate!<LF>She's just like you, Sunshine! Kah hah hah hah hah!
Like you're any different.
Eh?
Hate is just another crutch for you.
Hey now—
You're in pain. You're lonely. No one likes you.<LF>So you try to hide it under violence and hate.
I'm not like that at all!
It's okay.
...It is?
Look, I'm the same way.
But just realizing that isn't going to help.
It's too late for us now.
It's too late for everything. We're too far gone, you and me. That's why we—
This way! Hurry!
Dammit! I can't get it open!
The entrance is locked, too!
It seems we are in a bit of a predicament.
You will go no further.
We must protect our final bastion!
Strike the beast while it's down!
That fog... Oh, no!
We can't...stop now... Dammit...
Stay focused, Kainé!
How can we deal with this th-th-thing!?
Can we even hurt this thing!?
(Unseal the exit!)
(Let our friends through!)
(The People of the Mask owe you a great debt.)
(And now is the time to repay it!)
(Hah! They could stand to loosen up a bit, huh?)
What are you doing here!?
(My citizens were speaking of your latest adventure.)
(This is the castle of the Shadowlord, is it not?)
You are correct.
(Then we have a common enemy!)
(We'll hold this one off. Please keep moving!)
But...
(We are the People of the Mask.)
(We will stand our ground until our last breath.)
(I swore it upon Fyra's grave...)
(I swore to become a good and just ruler. A king who would protect others from the Shades.)
(It's open!)
(Now, go! Rescue the one you hold most dear!)
My friend...
You and us? We're the same! Tools in the hands of a master!
No! I'm nothing like you!
Please don't do this, Popola!
You and Devola were like parents to me!
Those two have watched the world wither for time immemorial. The cruelness of such a fate is difficult to imagine.
I don't want to do this. I don't want to fight her!
Stop bitching and start fighting! It's the only way!
This ends here!
Strike hard! Hold nothing back!
How could a mere tool hope to stand against the Shadowlord?
Don't speak in such a manner, fool! I am nothing like you!
...No. No! Impossible!
Be careful!
I know!
Hey, Sunshine? I ain't certain about this, but I think your heart is...evolving.
The hate is gone, the sadness is gone... It's just a buncha white light now.
What the hell's goin' on here!?
You can't tell, Tyrann?
You're not the only voice in my life anymore.
I've experienced fear, hate...and now sympathy.
I'm a curse. A freak. I know that.
But guess what? He still accepts me. He still <FONT=ITALIC>forgives</FONT> me.
Oh, come on! You're doin' this for HIM?
I'm tired of this world and everybody in it.
But I'll become his sword one last time!
Weiss! You all right!?
Naturally! I am as fit as a fid-id-id-id-id-iddle... Nnnngnnggghhh!
Yonah? Why?
Kainé! Watch over Yonah for me!
You want me to understand your sadness?
You think I'm gonna sympathize with you?
But why!?
I swore to protect my sister and my friends.
If someone puts them in danger, they must stand aside or be cut down!
Now come on! Let's finish this!
Noooooooo!
Weiss! What's wrong?
F-f-f-fine! All is weeeeeell... We-we-we-we-wellllll...
You're freaking me out here, Weiss!
Wh-wh-wh-what are you doing!?
To come so f-f-f-ar... D-d-do it! Strike the k-k-k-killing blow!
Aaaaaaaaargh!
Yonah... I cannot live...in a world without you...
I have something to defend! I have a reason to live!
Begone!
Shadowlord... You...
Yonah... Soon I will...join you...
I'm gonna swallow you up, Sunshine!
Gonna swallow you whole!
Tyrann! I don't want to hurt my friends!
Well, hell, Sunshine, it's not like I can stop it!
When Gestalts go out of control, they lose their minds!
Both of our memories will be completely overwritten!
H-hurry...
Kainé!
Run... RUN!
Ngh...ngh...
Dammit! I have to do something!
Kill...me...
I won't!
(You defeated the Shadowlord...)
(You rescued Yonah...)
(But now, I can't... I can't...)
We made it this far because you were with us, Kainé!
I'm who I am today because of you!
I'm not going to give up on you...
I'm not going to abandon someone I love!
I'm going to save you. I swear it!
Whew. Well, it's over. Better report back to the client.
First mechanical monsters, and now Shades! Has some manner of curse been placed on this mountain?
Hey, if there are Shades to kill, it's fine with me.
Um...
Here come some more!
They certainly are dedicated to this attack.
Be careful! This is a stronger Shade than the ones previous!
Careful, my ass! I'll slice this guy apart!
Mmm, yes. How assuring.
That's the last of them. Now let's get a piece of that tree root.
...It's dead. Let's go back to the client.
Now it makes sense. It attacked people by hiding in giant dust storms. That's pretty smart for a Shade.
We'd best warn the client about this Shade.
We've avenged the postmen. Let's go report back.
The Shades inside this temple are far more powerful than I expected...
Either way, our work here is done. Let's get back to the king.
Those Shades are tricky when they work together like that.
I doubt this will be the last time we see such a tactic.<LF>We'd best use caution in the future.
That was intense. No wonder they sealed that thing up.
Still, it should not have been our fight in the first place.
True enough. Let's grab the surviving bandit and take him back to Facade.
Is this it?
You have to get him out of there now!
I'm on it.
We're not going to lose anyone else!
Move... Move... Come on, you stupid arm, move!
(Come, wolves! Taste the sting of our blades! I'll leave not a single one of you alive!)
We can never forgive you, humans!
There shall never be peace between us!
(Please be careful, my liege!)
(We must protect the king and his advisor!)
(Avenge our comrades! Leave no wolf alive!)
(Pay heed to the guests of our king!)
(The size of the pack doesn't matter! Take out the leader and it will crumble!)
(Forget the other wolves! Focus your strength on the pack leader!)
Ah, just the man I wanted to see.
What is it?
I need you to purchase an item at The Aerie.
I want to fix the roof, but I need something called Valley Spider Silk.<LF>Can you handle that?
Are you referring to the village of cowards where none dare show their faces?
That's the one.
I doubt they're willing to do business with outsiders.
Apparently they've loosened up. I hear they even have a shop now
Why don't you poke around and see what you can find?
Aren't you glad to be going back home, Kainé?
Home?
That place is a shithole.
Don't be so nervous, Kainé. We'll protect you.
I got me taken care of! Worry about protecting yourself.
Oooh, the village! It's home to sooo many tewwible wittle memowies, isn't it, Kainé?<LF>KAAAH HAH HAH HAH HAH!
Shut up! Shut up, shut up!
You! I know you!
You will be destroyed! All of you!
I'm done believing in people.
My wife's been acting kind of...strange...
Ahhhh! There's nothing like a breath of fresh outdoor air!
What's the point? Nothing matters anymore.
Go away! We don't want to go outside!
I can't keep holing up inside; I'm gonna get fat!
I'm scared... Go away!
What do you want? Just leave me alone.
It's over... It's all over...
Eeeeaaghh!
Help me! Oh god, please help me!
The Shades! The Shades!
Hold! That one is not possessed!
Get away from me, you freak!
Stay back! Your sister is one of them now!
I don't care! She's my sister, and I love her.
Aaaaah! Kainé! I can't...I can't stand it!
Come on! Help me take it out!
I'm on it.
Its weak point is located around the back!<LF>Try attacking it from above!
You'd never know there was a path here!
The skill used in its construction boggles the mind.
Hmph! I detect not a hint of intelligence from within that clump of iron.
Who cares if it's smart when it can smash you into a pancake!?
No mere machine can hope to prevail against our intelligence and skill!
Wow, thanks, book. I feel so much better already.
Cultivating Lunar Tears must require a remarkable amount of work.
He really tried to get his lover to join him, didn't he?
It appears so. But who can say if that lover honestly wanted to wait?
What do you mean?
The woman wanted to live with him, did she not?
Well, yeah, but it wasn't gonna happen. That's why he left her in the village.
It would have been difficult, yes, but perhaps preferable to a life of solitude.
Why did they not think about how much the time and distance would separate them?
It doesn't matter anymore. They can see each other just fine now.
...Indeed.
She wasn't there.
No.
Guess you were right, Weiss.
I find it difficult to determine who is right at this point.
We had best return to him.
Waterwheels are great, but they're a pain in the butt to maintain!
In the past, humans harnessed different methods to provide energy.
Like what?
One of them was an invisible force called electricity which was transmitted through thin copper wires.
Wow! What did they do with that?
Oh, a great many things. It could be used to power large iron crates called trains, or illuminate whole cities against the dark of night.
Well, that's stupid.
Is it now?
Who wants to move a big iron crate? ...And how am I supposed to sleep if it's all bright outside?
Well, I suppose if you wish to look at it that way—
Besides, my life is lots of fun already!
If more people were like you, Emil, this world might not be half bad.
Hee hee!
Hey, Weiss, what was this big old bridge used for, anyway?
This? Ah, yes. This was a road for the large iron crates that I mentioned earlier.
Wow. Why is it so big?
The iron crates moved at high speed, and were crammed to the gills with cargo and people. Such large roads were necessary.
Really? With people?
Humans lived very differently long ago.
There must have been so many people here...
Haven't fished in a while, huh?
I am amazed that you have not grown weary of it yet.
Not really, no.
Hmm.
There's just something about catching a fish that makes you feel alive.
Perhaps you are forgetting the reason you went fishing in the first place.
Look, everyone needs a break sometimes.
I wonder if I've beaten that old fisherman yet.
One wonders how talented a fisherman he actually is.
You saw that chip on his shoulder! He must be amazing.
Have you actually seen him in action?
Uh...no.
...Well, off to fishing, then.
...Yeah.
All right, I'm gonna give it my all this time!
Have you been holding back?
I always give it my all!
Shhhhh! You're scaring them away!
Gahh...
I guess he's taught me everything he knows.
Oh? And what have you learned up to now?
Well, the...art of...perseverance?
That's hardly a skill which can be taught.
Well, I guess that's it.
This fishing certainly seems like fun.
Yeah, but it's work, too. Still, I'm grateful for everything that the old fisherman taught me.
I didn't even know the old guy was sick.
Perhaps that's why he was in such a hurry to pass down his craft.
This is strange, but I feel like he's still here somehow, looking at me.
I trust that he is in heaven by now, settling down for a round by the pond.
I hope you're right, Weiss.
It is fascinating how gourmet cuisine can survive even in the midst of a food shortage.
Well, of course! People like eating good food! It makes them happy.
What manner of food do you enjoy, Emil?

Well, I like vanilla custard cake, but if I had to choose between vanilla custard cake and vanilla crepes, I don't know what I'd do, because I really like them both. Oh, and I love chocolate cake, but it has to have ice cream on top. With sprinkles. And a cherry. No, wait! Two cherries! Oh, oh, and I also like fruit tarts, and crème brûlée, and those little pie things with the weird crumply crust on the edges. ...Oh, wait! I totally forgot about strawberry shortcake!<LF>Yeah, that's really good, too.
...I will not pretend to understand anything you just said, but I admire your dedication.
Thanks!
I wonder if these people use the same mask for life.
I hadn't thought about it. ...I hope they wash those things.
You've been wearing the same shitty clothes since I met you.
There is nothing more filthy than your underwear, hussy!
What, this? I don't wear the same one all the time. I have a different set for every day of the week.
And every night, I scrub them with soap and water. So you can bet your ass I'm cleaner than either of you!
My word...
It's hard to believe there are plants that can grow in this desert.
Yeah, this will never work.
How do you mean?
I mean if plants could grow here, it would be full of 'em! ...God, books can be so stupid sometimes.
Have you ever planted anything before, Kainé?
Nope.
Well, then you don't know! You gotta try things out for yourself!
Indeed! Experimentation can often be the key to new knowledge.
You guys sure are a bunch of optimists.
So you're going to fetch parts to fix a lighthouse?
Yeah. There was this old lady that helped me once, and I'm fixing the lighthouse where she used to live.
Exactly who did the helping is a matter of debate, but regardless...
Wow, a lighthouse keeper! That sounds kind of romantic!
Indeed, she was nothing if not a hopeless romantic.
Yeah, I guess she was.
It is filled with strange potions and documents.
Looks like some weapons, too. ...Whoa! That's a bomb!
What on earth was that old woman transporting?
A wise choice. Rifling through the possessions of others is a vulgar habit.
I'm still kinda curious about what's inside, though.
Medication and explosives again. Who can say what it is for?
A supply this size could provide for the military of a small country.
This much merchandise has to have a buyer, right?
It seems you humans are incapable of learning from the mistakes of the past...
I dare say, I can see no reason why the old woman would need this much baggage.
That's not for us to say.
That old woman, is it?
Yeah.
Perhaps a visit to her home is in order.
So the Mermaid Tear was being sent to her...
That thing must stir up some powerful memories.
But it is far too late to bring it to her now.
No, it's not.
...I certainly hope so.
Give it everything you got!
Ah, but...don't tire yourself out!
Find an opening and attack!
Show them the power of the Masked People!
You're doing fine! Just stay calm!
Focus on your foe! Be aware of his movements at all times!
Oh, I'm so happy he passed his examination!
...Yeah.
